on a glide path to the U.N. ambassadorship, and thus won=E2=80=99t be aroun=
d for tax bill negotiations. Three Republicans from
New York and at least one from California lost reelection two weeks ago. (W=
hen all the votes are counted, California might lose as many as three Repub=
lican incumbents.) Meanwhile, three members of the blue state Republican de=
legations currently sit on the Ways and Means Committee, which has jurisdic=
tion over federal tax law, where they=E2=80=99re ostensibly poised to influ=
ence the actual drafting of the bill: New York=E2=80=99s Claudia Tenney and=
 Nicole Malliotakis, along with Californian Michelle Steel. (Steel=E2=80=99=
s reelection race is still outstanding, however, and it=E2=80=99s unclear w=
hether she will be returning to the House.)

