mer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) the larger tax bill. All but one wer=
e from those big three blue states. In 2025, however, it=E2=80=99s likely t=
hat Speaker Mike Johnson and House Ways and Means Chairman Jason Smith won=
=E2=80=99t have 12 protest votes to spare. As with every other whip count, =
the tighter the margin, the more leverage each
individual member has.

So even though red state Republicans have the numbers advantage over their =
blue state brethren=E2=80=94to say nothing of Democrats=E2=80=94the margin =
will matter. The question is how much, and whether the beleaguered blue sta=
te Republicans, with Trump=E2=80=99s apparent backing, can leverage their m=
eager numbers to win a war they=E2=80=99ve been waging unsuccessfully for s=
even years. After all, this past Congress it only took a handful of members=
 to defenestrate then-Speaker Kevin McCarthy. This time, at least, the dram=
a will have nothing to do with Matt Gaetz.

